        heading: 'The Rahu-Ketu Axis in Practice',
        content: `Because Rahu and Ketu are always exactly opposite each other, they form an axis across two houses in the birth chart. This axis reveals the central tension of the soul's journey in this lifetime - moving from the comfort of what you know (Ketu) toward the unfamiliar territory you came here to explore (Rahu).\n\nFor example: Rahu in the 1st house / Ketu in the 7th. The soul has deep past-life experience with relationships and partnership (Ketu in 7th) and came into this life to develop a stronger individual identity (Rahu in 1st). This person may find relationships feel automatic or hollow, while the challenge of self-development feels magnetically alive.\n\nRahu in the 4th / Ketu in the 10th: The soul has mastered career and public status in past lives. This lifetime calls for developing inner security, home, and emotional roots - even if worldly achievement comes naturally and easily.\n\nUnderstanding your Rahu-Ketu axis gives you a map of your soul's curriculum for this lifetime.`,
