        content: `The zodiac in Vedic astrology is divided not only into 12 signs (Rashis) but also into 27 Nakshatras (lunar mansions), each spanning 13°20' of the zodiac. Because the Moon moves approximately one Nakshatra per day, your birth Nakshatra is highly specific and personally revealing.\n\nThe Nakshatra your Moon occupies at birth is called your Janma Nakshatra. It is used for: naming children (the name should begin with a syllable associated with the birth Nakshatra), calculating the Vimshottari Dasha starting point, determining compatibility in marriage (Ashta Kuta matching), and identifying the quality of mind and emotional nature in fine detail.\n\nFor example, Moon in Rohini Nakshatra produces a very different temperament than Moon in Ardra Nakshatra, even though both fall within Taurus and Gemini respectively. The Nakshatra adds a layer of precision that the sign alone cannot provide.`,
